  "prompt": "How is work life balance in wipro consumer care and lighting?",
  "response": "The work-life balance at Wipro Consumer Care and Lighting can vary based on several factors including the specific role, department, and location. However, here are some general insights that might help you understand what to expect:\n\n1. **Flexible Working Hours**: Wipro often offers flexible working hours, which can help employees manage their personal commitments alongside their professional responsibilities. This flexibility can significantly contribute to a better work-life balance.\n\n2. **Remote Work Options**: Like many companies today, Wipro has adapted to remote working arrangements, especially post the global shift due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This can reduce commute times and offer more freedom in managing daily schedules.\n\n3. **Work Culture**: Wipro's work culture is generally described as supportive with an emphasis on employee well-being. There are initiatives aimed at promoting mental health and overall wellness.\n\n4. **Leave Policies**: Wipro typically provides generous leave policies, including vacation time, sick leave, and various other types of leave, which can help employees take breaks when needed.\n\n5. **Departmental Variations**: Work-life balance can differ significantly between departments. For instance, roles in sales or product development might have more demanding schedules compared to roles in HR or administrative functions.\n\n6. **Employee Feedback**: Reviews on platforms like Glassdoor and Indeed often mention work-life balance. While some employees praise the company for its supportive environment, others might mention high-pressure periods that can affect balance.\n\nTo get the most accurate picture, it's advisable to speak with current or former employees, especially those in the specific role or department you're interested in. This will give you a clearer idea of what to expect in terms of work-life balance at Wipro Consumer Care and Lighting.",
